fix: inherit parent stderr instead of DEVNULL or file handle

Three attempts at stderr routing, here's why each failed:

1. stderr=DEVNULL: C-level crashes invisible. Workers die, no trace.
2. stderr=open(log_file): rapid concurrent spawns on Windows race
   between Popen inheriting the fd and parent closing it. 3 of 5
   workers got 0 bytes in their log files.
3. stderr=PIPE: pipe buffer fills if nobody reads it (64KB Windows).
   Worker hangs on write.

Correct answer: inherit parent stderr (no stderr= kwarg).
Worker main() redirects sys.stderr to its own log file as the
first action. Pre-redirect crashes go to MCP server stderr.
